<div class="bg-darkblue p-5 my-5">
<div class="container-md">
<h2>Best Sports Betting Sites North America</h2>
<div class="row">
<div class="col-12 col-md-8 usamap-info">
<p>Currently, the online sports betting market in the United States brings multimillion-dollar budget revenues and sees constant growth. Despite occasional crises, the US online betting market is relatively stable and recovers quickly from shocks. If you look at the situation with the COVID-19 pandemic, things have turned out to be fairly positive for online bookies: after a slight drop in income, the market quickly recovered and showed even better results.</p>
<p>Against this background, new online bookmakers keep entering the business. On this <a href="/">sportsbook reviews site</a>, you can learn about the newcomers to the market and reputable betting sites providing high-quality services to US players. Find out everything you need to choose a secure bookmaker with the sweetest sports bonuses, convenient deposit/withdrawal methods, a wide betting line, and much more.</p>
</div>
<div class="col-12 col-md-4 usamap"> </div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="container-md">
<h2>Top Betting Bonuses for North America Players</h2>
<p>The best thing about offshore online bookmakers is the range of bonuses they offer. Promotions are the main marketing tools that attract new clients and help keep regular bettors engaged. A set of bonus offers is among the most important features to consider when choosing a betting site. Get an insight into the most popular deals designed for newcomers and active players.</p>
<h3>Welcome Bonus</h3>
<p>Whatever bookie you join will most likely have a welcome package. Also known as a sign-up bonus, it’s available only once after registration. As soon as you create an account and verify it, you need to make the minimum required deposit to claim it.</p>
<p>Some welcome deals are activated automatically. However, the player may need to provide a special promo code to unlock the bonus, so it is better to check the bookie’s T&amp;C in advance. Typically, the bookmaker matches the amount you deposit. A 100% match bonus, for example, will double your first top-up, so if you cash in 100 USD, you’ll get the same amount on top of that.</p>
<p>Keep in mind that the bonus amount has an upper limit. If the bookie offers you a 100% match bonus of up to 1,000 USD, it means you can’t receive more than 1,000 USD, no matter how much you deposit. According to welcome promo rules, you can’t withdraw bonus money immediately. Instead, you need to use it to place bets, following wagering requirements. For instance, you may need to place only single bets at odds of 1.5+, and the bet amount can’t exceed 20 USD.</p>
<p>There’s also a certain wager multiplier, meaning that, before you’re allowed to withdraw the bonus, the total amount of real money bets you place must be 5 or 10 times larger than the amount you received from the promo, depending on the requirements. Like most bonuses, the welcome promo has an expiration date that you should consider.</p>
<h3>Reload Bonus</h3>
<p>Unlike the welcome promo, not all bookies have this bonus deal. Often, sportsbooks add it during important sports events. Within this promo, players can receive a certain amount of money on top of their deposit or get a free bet.</p>
<p>In the case of a match bonus, its percentage is significantly less than what you can get with the sign-up bonus deal (most betting sites do not offer over 25%). In order to withdraw winnings from a reload bonus, you must also meet wagering requirements before the promo expires.</p>
<h3>Free Bet</h3>
<p>This is the second most common bonus type. Its name says it all: the bookie gives you a chance to place one or several bets for free. This bonus always has a maximum bet cap of around 5-10 USD and comes with wagering requirements, so it’s better to check the Terms &amp; Conditions before using it.</p>
<h3>Cashback</h3>
<p>As the name suggests, you can get a percentage of the sum you lost while betting. As a rule, the upper limit for this promo is capped at 10%. Depending on the cashback type, players can get a percentage on the amount they lose over a day, week, or month.</p>
<h3>No-Deposit Bonus</h3>
<p>This promotion is quite rare. As you might’ve guessed, you don’t have to deposit anything in order to get it. Usually, bookmakers give no-deposit bonuses for certain actions, like subscribing to their social media or installing their apps. This may be a small cash bonus of around 10-20 USD or a free bet. Along with the obvious advantages of this promotion, there’s also a major drawback: in most cases, it comes with a high wager (up to 70x, compared to the usual 5x).</p>
<h2>Common Deposit and Withdrawal Methods</h2>
<p>All modern betting sites support a plethora of payment methods you can use to deposit funds and withdraw winnings. Along with fiat money, modern bookies accept various cryptocurrencies. Below, you can learn more about the most popular payment methods supported by offshore bookmakers.</p>
<h3>E-wallets</h3>
<div class="row">
<div class="col-12 col-sm-9">
<p>This is one of the most convenient tools for depositing money or withdrawing winnings. E-wallets allow users to store data from one or more banking methods and move money more freely. They essentially act as an intermediary between the bookmaker and the player.</p>
<p>To carry out the transaction, you just need to log into your account without having to enter banking information. Also, e-wallets offer a high level of personal data protection since all confidential info about your bank account is kept away from the bookmaker. The most popular e-wallets available on betting sites are Neteller, Skrill, and PayPal.</p>
</div>
<div class="col-12 col-sm-3 order-first order-sm-last text-center"><img class="payment-ico" src="/wp-content/uploads/sportsbookreviewsonline_com_737/payment-method-ewallet.svg" alt="ewallet betting sites"></div>
</div>
<h3>(ACH) VIP-Preferred e-Check</h3>
<div class="row">
<div class="col-12 col-sm-9">
<p>This method is less popular compared to digital wallets. Often, you can find this option on the “Preferred VIP” list on legal betting sites. This service offers incredibly fast deposit and withdrawal times. However, depending on your bank’s policy, funds may not be debited from your account immediately. On average, the deposit will be credited within 2-3 days after the transaction. Another feature of this financial gateway is fixed limits.</p>
</div>
<div class="col-12 col-sm-3 order-first order-sm-last text-center"><img class="payment-ico" src="/wp-content/uploads/sportsbookreviewsonline_com_737/payment-method-check.svg" alt="check betting sites"></div>
</div>
<h3>Debit and Credit Cards</h3>
<div class="row">
<div class="col-12 col-sm-9">
<p>This is the most common financial gateway for deposits and cashouts. The key advantage of this payment method is the ease of use: the whole process of depositing or withdrawing doesn’t take much time since no third parties are involved.</p>
<p>At the same time, you should always check your bank’s policy regarding betting and gambling-related financial transactions. Sometimes the funds you deposit may be considered cash advances, resulting in additional transaction fees. Among the most popular credit and debit cards supported at online bookies are Visa, MasterCard, And American Express.</p>
</div>
<div class="col-12 col-sm-3 order-first order-sm-last text-center"><img class="payment-ico" src="/wp-content/uploads/sportsbookreviewsonline_com_737/payment-method-card.svg" alt="debit cards betting sites"></div>
</div>
<h3>Prepaid Cards for Bettors</h3>
<div class="row">
<div class="col-12 col-sm-9">
<p>Though not as popular as bank cards and e-wallets, this method is supported by almost every online bookmaker. Among the striking examples of these financial gateways is Play+. Bettors who activate a prepaid card on a betting site will receive both access to their Play+ digital card and a physical copy of the card by mail.</p>
<p>The Play+ digital card is usually used as an intermediary between the user’s credit or debit card and the bookmaker. This is often necessary since many banks tend to reject deposits related to gambling and betting. Instead of depositing funds to the bookmaker, the player can send money to the prepaid Play+ card and then transfer it to their accounts.</p>
</div>
<div class="col-12 col-sm-3 order-first order-sm-last text-center"> </div>
</div>
<h2>Bitcoin Sportsbooks</h2>
<div class="row">
<div class="col-12 col-sm-9">
<p>Currently, a lot of betting sites available in the US accept cryptocurrency along with fiat money for deposits and withdrawals. Some bookmakers go even further and focus on crypto only. While there are lots of cryptocurrencies available today, Bitcoin, Litecoin, and Ethereum are the most popular and supported by most bookies. Below, you can check the list of the main pros of <a href="/crypto-sports-betting/">crypto betting sites</a>.</p>
<ul>
<li>decentralization — all transactions are performed without any third-party regulator (only you have control over the process);</li>
<li>speed of transactions — all deposits are submitted and performed almost immediately;</li>
<li>security — you don’t need to provide personal data to submit the transaction (also, there are no chargebacks);</li>
<li>zero transaction fees — this option is available thanks to no intermediary involved (the only exception is if you want to convert BTC into fiat money or speed up the process).</li>
</ul>
<p>To check whether a particular bookie supports transactions with crypto, visit its cashier section, read the T&amp;Cs, or contact customer support.</p>
</div>
<div class="col-12 col-sm-3 order-first order-sm-last text-center"><img style="max-width: 120px;" src="/wp-content/uploads/sportsbookreviewsonline_com_737/payment-method-bitcoin.svg" alt="bitcoin betting sites"></div>
</div>
<h2>Which Sportsbooks Offer the Most Competitive Odds?</h2>
<p>All betting sites listed above are trusted and deserve your attention. They offer some of the best odds available in the market. However, if you compare odds between these bookies, you’ll find out that <a href="/bovada/">Bovada</a> has the highest odds both for pre-match and live betting.</p>
<h2>How to Sign Up at the Online Sportsbook in North America?</h2>
<p>No matter what online betting site you choose, the process of signing up is fairly similar. Below, you can get an insight into the main steps you need to take to create an account.</p>
<ol>
<li>Select the online bookmaker you would like to join.</li>
<li>Click on the registration button (usually located in the upper right corner of the screen).</li>
<li>Fill in a registration form to provide the bookie with basic information about yourself (email, phone number, currency type, and so on).</li>
<li>Agree to the bookie’s Terms and Conditions and click to submit the action.</li>
</ol>
<p>After that, check your email. There should be a message from the bookmaker with an attached link: click on it to verify your email address and become a full member. After that, you can visit the cashier’s section, top up your balance and start betting on your favorite sports team.</p>
<p>The most important thing when registering is to provide the correct personal information. The bookmaker may request ID verification, so you’ll need to submit the documents confirming your identity, banking information, and address. If the info you provided during registration doesn’t match that from your documents, the bookmaker may deny any withdrawals or block your account.</p>
<h2>Choosing the Best Bookmaker: Tips &amp; Tricks</h2>
<p>While choosing the top online bookmaker, it’s important to consider a set of crucial features, which are described below.</p>
<h3>Security</h3>
<p>Identity theft is no joke, so the security of your personal/financial data is an essential feature. Make sure that the bookmaker has a relevant license issued by reputable regulators and offers SSL encryption. You can find this info in the site’s T&amp;C or by contacting customer support.</p>
<h3>Betting Odds Value</h3>
<p>This factor matters because it impacts your potential winnings. These odds directly depend on the marginal percentage, which is laid out in the bets. Consistently, the lower the percentage of margin, the greater the odds for the players.</p>
<h3>Variety of Markets</h3>
<p>A wide selection of sports is another sign of a bookie’s credibility and reputation. Choose those sportsbooks that offer the maximum betting markets with events within local and world tournaments, different bet types (single, express, chain, accumulator), and so on.</p>
<h3>Available Payment Methods</h3>
<p>You’ll hardly want to lose a portion of your money to transaction fees or come across too strict limits or payment delays. Besides, there’s no point in creating a Skrill e-wallet if you already have PayPal. So be sure to check if the bookmaker supports the banking options you need. Plus, if the bookie allows deposits and withdrawals via bank cards and multiple other payment gateways, it’s another sign of its reliability.</p>
<h3>Customer Support Service</h3>
<p>A customer care system is important when you face technical or financial issues. You should have reliable communication channels to contact the bookie’s specialist and resolve the problem within the shortest time possible (live chat, email, social media, and a hotline).</p>
<h2>Key Features of Offshore Bookmakers</h2>
<p>Below, you can check the main advantages and drawbacks of overseas bookmakers to have a better understanding of how to select the right one.</p>
<div class="row bg-white mb-3">
<div class="col-12 col-sm-6 p-3">
<h3 class="text-success">Pros:</h3>
<ul class="pros">
<li>A wide range of payment methods, including those which support cryptocurrency;</li>
<li>low taxes on withholding;</li>
<li>a wider range of sports events;</li>
<li>better privacy;</li>
<li>tempting bonus offers.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="col-12 col-sm-6 p-3">
<h3 class="text-danger">Cons:</h3>
<ul class="cons">
<li>can be difficult to deposit via bank cards;</li>
<li>does not comply with the same strict rules related to data security as regulated bookies;</li>
<li>players are responsible for documenting wins/losses and reporting in tax returns (no automatic report).</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<p>Apart from that, depending on the license issuer, potential conflicts with the bookmaker may not be resolved in your favor.</p>
<h2>Legal Aspects of Online Betting in the North America</h2>
<p>There are no federal laws that prohibit players from registering and placing bets on offshore online bookmakers (if they comply with all required rules and norms and have a relevant license). However, the situation may vary from state to state where penalties for violating gambling laws may lead to serious consequences, from fines to imprisonment.</p>
